-- Terra of Mauritius Plans Bottling Plant in India, l’Express Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-08-07T06:25:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/terra-of-mauritius-plans-bottling-plant-in-india-l-express-says.html
Grays Inc., a unit of  Terra Mauricia
Ltd. (TERA) , plans to operate a wine and spirits bottling plant in
India by the end of the year with an Indian company, l’Express
reported, citing Director General Alain Vallet.  Grays, which distills and bottles spirits, plans to
increase revenue from overseas operations to 60 percent from 10
percent, the Port Louis-based newspaper reported,without
stipulating the period. Profit growth in 2012 is expected to
range from 3 percent to 6 percent, it said, citing Vallet.
Income for fiscal 2011 was 3.5 billion rupees ($113 million), it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
